article.description: — Derrick Alston Jr. had 16 points and seven rebounds as Boise State extended its win streak to nine games, defeating Air Force 78-59 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Alston Jr. carries Boise St. past Air Force 78-59
article.linkText: Alston Jr. carries Boise St. past Air Force 78-59
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- — Derrick Alston Jr. had 16 points and seven rebounds as Boise State extended its win streak to nine games, defeating Air Force 78-59 on Wednesday night. Marcus Shaver Jr. had 15 points for Boise State (9-1, 5-0 Mountain West Conference). Max Rice added 12 points. RayJ Dennis had 10 points. A.J. Walker had 16 points for the Falcons (3-6, 1-4). Keaton Van Soelen added 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
